                &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;!-- /.row --&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;

        &lt;!-- /.container --&gt;
    &lt;/section&gt;

[/code]

Each menu item is a Bootstrap container located in order from top to bottom on the page. When the "About" menu item is clicked the Bootstrap container containing the About section is scrolled into view.
<h5>Step 3: CSS</h5>
The CSS is used to style the menu and the menu items and to set the menu sizing and behavior when it opens and closes. The CSS code in the stylish-portfolio.css file is used to style the menu. The sidebar-wrapper CSS contains the size of the overall menu and the timing for the menu transitioning to open and to close (0.4 seconds in this case):

&nbsp;

[code language="css"]
/* Side Menu */

#sidebar-wrapper {
    z-index: 1000;
    position: fixed;
    right: 0;
    width: 250px;
    height: 100%;
    transform: translateX(250px);
    overflow-y: auto;
    background: #222;
    -webkit-transition: all 0.4s ease 0s;
    -moz-transition: all 0.4s ease 0s;
    -ms-transition: all 0.4s ease 0s;
    -o-transition: all 0.4s ease 0s;
    transition: all 0.4s ease 0s;
}
[/code]

The "sidebar-nav" section contains details about the interior of the menu such as the text sizing, indentation, list ordering, color and mouse over and click display characteristics:

[code language="css"]
.sidebar-nav {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
